Description: Global push-to-hold voice input for Linux/Wayland
 Hold right-Ctrl, speak, release: the recognised text is pasted into
 the currently-focused input field. Backed by Doubao's streaming ASR.
 .
 This package installs the Python application, a systemd --user service
 for auto-start, and a postinst hook that:
   * adds the installing user to the 'input' group so /dev/input/event*
     and /dev/uinput are reachable without sudo, and
   * creates a user-level venv at ~/.local/share/doubao-input/.venv
     containing the pure-Python deps (websockets, sounddevice, evdev),
     because those are not in Ubuntu's apt repos for python3-* .